\‘Look, Master, at this realm of flowers and happy creatures -- of phoenixes,
cranes and deer. Is it not a better place indeed than the haunted deserts
through which you and I have passed?’ Tripitaka still murmured his thanks, and
with a strange feeling of lightness and exhilaration they all set off up the
Holy Mountain.
